<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-06-22T02:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-06-22T02:00:00-05:00" n="86" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d86">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">124.83/86: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Cairo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-06-22T10:00:00+03:00">June 22,
                                    1942—10 a.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 11:19 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1048. Evacuation plans which were prepared months ago are complete
                            insofar as is possible with the exception of the name of the country
                            which would take over American interests in case of evacuation. May I
                            assume that Switzerland is indicated?</p>
                        <p>It is obvious that the matter should be kept secret as my first
                            preoccupation at the present moment is to avoid any action here which
                            might smack of panic. I submit that the question might be settled
                            between Washington and Bern on the understanding that instructions be
                            not sent to the Swiss Chargé here unless and until circumstances
                            require.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Kirk</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>